title: Most Effective Control of Corruption
description: In 2023, Finland achieved a perfect score of 100 in the Control of Corruption percentile rank, indicating an exceptionally low level of corruption.

title: Cleanest Air Quality
description: With a mean annual PM2.5 exposure of just 4.9 micrograms per cubic meter in 2020, Finland boasts one of the cleanest air qualities globally.

title: Universal Financial Inclusion for Older Adults
description: By 2021, 100% of Finland's population aged 25 and above had access to financial institutions or mobile money services.

title: Universal Financial Inclusion for Educated Population
description: In 2021, all individuals aged 15+ with secondary education or more had access to financial services in Finland.

title: High Investment in Research and Development
description: In 2020, 71% of Finnish firms reported spending on research and development, highlighting a strong focus on innovation.

title: Efficient Logistics Performance
description: Finland scored 4.1 in 2022 for ease of arranging competitively priced shipments, reflecting a robust logistics sector.

title: Timely Shipment Deliveries
description: In 2022, Finland achieved a score of 4.3 for the frequency of shipments reaching their destination on time.

title: Strong Rule of Law
description: Finland's rule of law was highly rated in 2023, with a percentile rank of 100 and an estimate of 1.97.

title: High Female Secondary School Enrollment
description: In 2022, Finland's female secondary school enrollment rate was 153.2%, indicating widespread access to education.

title: Low Mortality from Air Pollution
description: In 2019, Finland reported a mortality rate of 5.1 per 100,000 females due to air pollution, one of the lowest globally.

title: Low Tuberculosis Treatment Success Rate
description: In 2022, Finland had a tuberculosis treatment success rate of just 1%, indicating challenges in this health area.

title: High Contraceptive Prevalence
description: In 2015, 85.5% of married women aged 15-49 in Finland used any contraceptive method, reflecting widespread access to family planning.

title: Minimal Child Marriage
description: By 2017, only 0.1% of Finnish women aged 20-24 were married by age 18, showcasing effective child protection policies.
